def clean_feature_names(df):
    df.columns = [col.replace(' ', '_').replace('[', '').replace(']', '').replace('<', '') for col in df.columns]
    return df
# After creating dummies, the model was not able to elaborate certain columns due to the presence of special characters

Boosting alghoritms and Hyperparameters tuning using k-fold cross validation

First alghorithm: LightGBM
In[]:
def objective(trial): 
    #
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)  # Splits the dataset into train and test sets with an 80-20 split.
    XX = pd.get_dummies(pd.concat([X_train, X_test], sort=False))  # Concatenates train and test sets to create dummy variables for all categorical features.
    X_train, X_test = XX.loc[X_train.index], XX.loc[X_test.index]  # Restores the train and test sets based on their original indices.

    X_train = clean_feature_names(X_train)  # Cleans the feature names in the training set.
    X_test = clean_feature_names(X_test)  # Cleans the feature names in the test set.

    X_train, X_test = X_train.align(X_test, join='inner', axis=1)  # Aligns train and test sets to ensure they have the same columns.

    scale_pos_weight = len(y[y == 0]) / len(y[y == 1])  # Calculates the positive class weight to handle class imbalance.

    # Defines the hyperparameters for LightGBM.
    params = {
        'n_estimators': trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 100, 300),  # Number of trees in the model.
        'learning_rate': trial.suggest_loguniform('learning_rate', 0.001, 0.2),  # Learning rate to shrink the contribution of each tree.
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 5, 15),  # Maximum depth of the tree.
        'num_leaves': trial.suggest_int('num_leaves', 20, 40),  # Maximum number of leaves per tree.
        'min_child_samples': trial.suggest_int('min_child_samples', 10, 50),  # Minimum number of samples a node must have to be split.
        'subsample': trial.suggest_float('subsample', 0.8, 1.0),  # Fraction of data to be used for fitting each tree.
        'subsample_freq': trial.suggest_int('subsample_freq', 0, 7),  # Frequency of subsampling.
        'colsample_bytree': trial.suggest_float('colsample_bytree', 0.6, 1.0),  # Fraction of features to be used for fitting each tree.
        'reg_alpha': trial.suggest_float('reg_alpha', 0.0, 1.0),  # L1 regularization term to prevent overfitting.
        'reg_lambda': trial.suggest_float('reg_lambda', 0.0, 1.0),  # L2 regularization term to prevent overfitting.
        'max_bin': trial.suggest_int('max_bin', 200, 300),  # Maximum number of bins to bucket continuous features.
        'scale_pos_weight': scale_pos_weight,  # Weight for the positive class to handle imbalance.
        'force_col_wise': True,  # Forces LightGBM to use column-wise data format.
        'verbosity': -1  # Sets the verbosity level (silent mode).
    }

    kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)  # Stratified K-Fold cross-validation to maintain class proportions in each fold.
    scores = []

    for train_index, val_index in kf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_fold_train, X_fold_val = X_train.iloc[train_index], X_train.iloc[val_index]  # Splits the train set into training and validation folds.
        y_fold_train, y_fold_val = y_train.iloc[train_index], y_train.iloc[val_index]  # Splits the labels correspondingly.

        model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(**params)  # Initializes the LightGBM model with the defined hyperparameters.
        model.fit(X_fold_train, y_fold_train)  # Trains the model on the training fold.
        probas = model.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1]  # Predicts probabilities for the validation fold.
        top_indices = np.argsort(probas)[-1698:]  # Sorts probabilities in descending order and selects the top 1698 (about 1/6 of the total).
        top_positives = y_fold_val.iloc[top_indices].sum()  # Counts the number of positive classes in the top 1698.
        total_positives = y_fold_val.sum()  # Counts the total number of positive classes in the validation fold.
        scores.append(top_positives / total_positives if total_positives > 0 else 0)  # Calculates the ratio of top positives to total positives and appends to scores list.

    return np.mean(scores)  # Returns the mean score across all folds.

sampler = optuna.samplers.TPESampler(seed=42)  # Initializes the TPE Sampler for Bayesian optimization with Optuna.
study = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', sampler=sampler)  # Creates an Optuna study to maximize the objective function.
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=50)  # Optimizes the objective function for 50 trials.

best_params = study.best_params  # Retrieves the best hyperparameters found.
best_score = study.best_value  # Retrieves the best score achieved.

print("Best Hyperparameters:", best_params)
print("Best Score for Top 50,000:", best_score)

history_plot = vis.plot_optimization_history(study)  # Creates a plot of the optimization history.
history_plot.show()

importance_plot = vis.plot_param_importances(study)  # Creates a plot of hyperparameter importances.
importance_plot.show()

slice_plot = vis.plot_slice(study)  # Creates a slice plot to visualize hyperparameter effects.
slice_plot.show()

train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(best_lgb_classifier, X_train, y_train, cv=5, scoring='recall', n_jobs=-1, train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10))
train_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
train_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
test_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
test_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_mean - train_std, train_mean + train_std, color='r', alpha=0.1)
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_mean - test_std, test_mean + test_std, color='g', alpha=0.1)
plt.plot(train_sizes, train_mean, 'o-', color='r', label='Training score')
plt.plot(train_sizes, test_mean, 'o-', color='g', label='Cross-validation score')
plt.xlabel('Training Size')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.title('Learning Curve')
plt.legend(loc="best")
plt.show()

In[]:
def objective(trial):
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)
    XX = pd.get_dummies(pd.concat([X_train, X_test], sort=False))
    X_train, X_test = XX.loc[X_train.index], XX.loc[X_test.index]

    X_train = clean_feature_names(X_train)
    X_test = clean_feature_names(X_test)

    X_train, X_test = X_train.align(X_test, join='inner', axis=1)

    scale_pos_weight = len(y[y == 0]) / len(y[y == 1])
    params = {
        'n_estimators': trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 100, 1000),
        'learning_rate': trial.suggest_loguniform('learning_rate', 0.01, 0.5),
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 3, 10),
        'min_child_weight': trial.suggest_int('min_child_weight', 1, 10),
        'subsample': trial.suggest_float('subsample', 0.5, 1.0),
        'colsample_bytree': trial.suggest_float('colsample_bytree', 0.5, 1.0),
        'gamma': trial.suggest_float('gamma', 0, 5),
        'reg_alpha': trial.suggest_float('reg_alpha', 0, 5),
        'reg_lambda': trial.suggest_float('reg_lambda', 0.1, 10),
        'scale_pos_weight': scale_pos_weight, 
        'verbosity': 0
    }

    kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    scores = []

    for train_index, val_index in kf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_fold_train, X_fold_val = X_train.iloc[train_index], X_train.iloc[val_index]
        y_fold_train, y_fold_val = y_train.iloc[train_index], y_train.iloc[val_index]

        model = xgb.XGBClassifier(**params)
        model.fit(X_fold_train, y_fold_train)
        probas = model.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1] 
        top_indices = np.argsort(probas)[-1698:]  
        top_positives = y_fold_val.iloc[top_indices].sum() 
        total_positives = y_fold_val.sum() 
        scores.append(top_positives / total_positives if total_positives > 0 else 0)  

    return np.mean(scores)

sampler = optuna.samplers.TPESampler(seed=42)
study = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', sampler=sampler)
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=50)

best_params = study.best_params
best_score = study.best_value

print("Best Hyperparameters:", best_params)
print("Best Score for Top 50,000:", best_score)


history_plot = vis.plot_optimization_history(study)
history_plot.show()

importance_plot = vis.plot_param_importances(study)
importance_plot.show()

slice_plot = vis.plot_slice(study)
slice_plot.show()

It's important to verify if the model is in overfittting. Through the use of the learning curve, we can see in the trained data and the tested data converge: if this happen, the model can summarize good the data, without overfitting. If the two curves remain far, there could be the overfitting risk. The metric used for the comparison is the Recall.
In[]:
train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(best_xgb_classifier, X_train_final, y_train_final, cv=5, scoring='recall', n_jobs=-1, train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10))
train_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
train_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
test_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
test_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_mean - train_std, train_mean + train_std, color='r', alpha=0.1)
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_mean - test_std, test_mean + test_std, color='g', alpha=0.1)
plt.plot(train_sizes, train_mean, 'o-', color='r', label='Training score')
plt.plot(train_sizes, test_mean, 'o-', color='g', label='Cross-validation score')
plt.xlabel('Training Size')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.title('Learning Curve')
plt.legend(loc="best")
plt.show()

In[]:
def objective(trial):
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)
    XX = pd.get_dummies(pd.concat([X_train, X_test], sort=False))
    X_train, X_test = XX.loc[X_train.index], XX.loc[X_test.index]

    X_train = clean_feature_names(X_train)
    X_test = clean_feature_names(X_test)

    X_train, X_test = X_train.align(X_test, join='inner', axis=1)

    scale_pos_weight = len(y[y == 0]) / len(y[y == 1])

    params = {
        'n_estimators': trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 100, 500),
        'learning_rate': trial.suggest_float('learning_rate', 0.01, 0.2, log=True),
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 5, 15),
        'l2_leaf_reg': trial.suggest_float('l2_leaf_reg', 1e-3, 10),
        'border_count': trial.suggest_int('border_count', 32, 255),
        'grow_policy': trial.suggest_categorical('grow_policy', ['SymmetricTree', 'Depthwise', 'Lossguide']),
        'min_data_in_leaf': trial.suggest_int('min_data_in_leaf', 1, 50),
        'leaf_estimation_iterations': trial.suggest_int('leaf_estimation_iterations', 1, 10),
        'leaf_estimation_method': trial.suggest_categorical('leaf_estimation_method', ['Newton', 'Gradient']),
        'scale_pos_weight': scale_pos_weight, 
        'verbose': False
    }

    kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    scores = []

    for train_index, val_index in kf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_fold_train, X_fold_val = X_train.iloc[train_index], X_train.iloc[val_index]
        y_fold_train, y_fold_val = y_train.iloc[train_index], y_train.iloc[val_index]

        model = cb.CatBoostClassifier(**params)
        model.fit(X_fold_train, y_fold_train)
        probas = model.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1] 
        top_indices = np.argsort(probas)[-1698:]  
        top_positives = y_fold_val.iloc[top_indices].sum() 
        total_positives = y_fold_val.sum() 
        scores.append(top_positives / total_positives if total_positives > 0 else 0)  

    return np.mean(scores)

sampler = optuna.samplers.TPESampler(seed=42)
study = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', sampler=sampler)
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=50)

best_params = study.best_params
best_score = study.best_value

print("Best Hyperparameters:", best_params)
print("Best Score for Top 50,000:", best_score)


history_plot = vis.plot_optimization_history(study)
history_plot.show()

importance_plot = vis.plot_param_importances(study)
importance_plot.show()

slice_plot = vis.plot_slice(study)
slice_plot.show()

train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(best_catboost_classifier, X_train_final, y_train_final, cv=5, scoring='recall', n_jobs=-1, train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10))
train_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
train_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
test_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
test_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_mean - train_std, train_mean + train_std, color='r', alpha=0.1)
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_mean - test_std, test_mean + test_std, color='g', alpha=0.1)
plt.plot(train_sizes, train_mean, 'o-', color='r', label='Training score')
plt.plot(train_sizes, test_mean, 'o-', color='g', label='Cross-validation score')
plt.xlabel('Training Size')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.title('Learning Curve')
plt.legend(loc="best")
plt.show()

Forth Method: 'Merging' of the previous three methods with a respective weight

In[]:
def objective(trial):
    # Assuming X and y are your features and labels respectively
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)
    XX = pd.get_dummies(pd.concat([X_train, X_test], sort=False))
    X_train, X_test = XX.loc[X_train.index], XX.loc[X_test.index]

    X_train = clean_feature_names(X_train)
    X_test = clean_feature_names(X_test)

    X_train, X_test = X_train.align(X_test, join='inner', axis=1)

    weight_catboost = trial.suggest_float('weight_catboost', 0, 1)
    weight_xgb = trial.suggest_float('weight_xgb', 0, 1 - weight_catboost)

    # Calculate weight for LightGBM as the remainder
    weight_lgbm = 1 - weight_catboost - weight_xgb

    kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    scores = []

    for train_index, val_index in kf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_fold_train, X_fold_val = X_train.iloc[train_index], X_train.iloc[val_index]
        y_fold_train, y_fold_val = y_train.iloc[train_index], y_train.iloc[val_index]

        catboost_predictions = best_catboost_classifier.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1]
        xgb_predictions = best_xgb_classifier.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1]
        lgbm_predictions = best_lgb_classifier.predict_proba(X_fold_val)[:, 1]
        ensemble_predictions = (weight_catboost * catboost_predictions) + (weight_xgb * xgb_predictions) + (weight_lgbm * lgbm_predictions)

        top_indices = np.argsort(ensemble_predictions)[-1698:]  
        top_positives = y_fold_val.iloc[top_indices].sum() 
        total_positives = y_fold_val.sum() 
        scores.append(top_positives / total_positives if total_positives > 0 else 0)  

    return np.mean(scores)

sampler = optuna.samplers.TPESampler(seed=42)
study = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', sampler=sampler)
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=50)

best_params = study.best_params
best_score = study.best_value

print("Best Hyperparameters:", best_params)
print("Best Score for Top 50,000:", best_score)


history_plot = vis.plot_optimization_history(study)
history_plot.show()

importance_plot = vis.plot_param_importances(study)
importance_plot.show()

slice_plot = vis.plot_slice(study)
slice_plot.show()

plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()
In[]:
catboost_pred = best_catboost_classifier.predict(X_test_final)
xgb_pred = best_xgb_classifier.predict(X_test_final)
lgbm_pred = best_lgb_classifier.predict(X_test_final)

y_pred = (weight_catboost * catboost_pred) + (weight_xgb * xgb_pred) + (weight_lgbm * lgbm_pred)
y_pred_binary = np.where(y_pred > 0.5, 1, 0)

cm = confusion_matrix(y_test_final, y_pred_binary)
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap='Blues')
plt.xlabel('Predicted Labels')
plt.ylabel('True Labels')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
plt.show()
